text: Mohamed Boudiaf (23 June 1919 - 29 June 1992, ; ALA-LC: Muḥammad Bū-Ḍiyāf), also called Si Tayeb el Watani, was an Algerian political leader and one of the founders of the revolutionary National Liberation Front (FLN). He was Chairman of the High Council of State, and was assassinated four months later. ==References== Category:1919 births Category:1992 deaths Category:Presidents of Algeria Category:Assassinated people
title: Mohamed Boudiaf
